handong province and performing data analysis and international project support as a research associate at harvard's school of public health her current projects include deworming efforts among chinese schoolchildren and providing vitamin supplements to mothers and infants publications the limits of health and nutrition education evidence from three randomized controlled trials in rural china renfu luo yaojiang shi linxiu zhang huiping zhang grant miller alexis medina scott rozelle pdf+ a cluster randomized trial of provider incentives for anemia reduction in rural china grant miller renfu luo linxiu zhang sean sylvia yaojiang shi patricia foo qiran zhao reynaldo martorell alexis medina scott rozelle intestinal roundworm infections and determining correlates in preschool and school aged children in southwest china xiaobing wang alexis medina linxiu zhang renfu luo guofei wang yingdan chen karen eggleston d scott smith scott rozelle research programs & projects rural education action program reap fsi stanford fse program search fse search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4920 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
